WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:03.587
PROFESSOR: You need to tap
into something more specific

00:03.587 --> 00:05.547
to push yourself to your full potential.

00:05.547 --> 00:08.217
- It feels like you've been
really weird with me lately.

00:08.217 --> 00:10.135
- It doesn't have anything to do with you.

00:10.135 --> 00:12.888
- I just wanna feel so normal.

00:12.888 --> 00:14.223
- I know what you mean.

00:14.223 --> 00:15.807
DIANA:
Why is that freshman calling you?

00:15.807 --> 00:17.893
- Wrigley keeps bringing her around.

00:17.893 --> 00:20.270
- I accidentally hooked up with him.

00:20.270 --> 00:21.355
- Wrigley?

00:21.355 --> 00:23.023
LUCY:
It's a memorial for Macy.

00:25.234 --> 00:26.568
STEPHEN:
This one won't die.

00:26.568 --> 00:29.488
♪

00:29.488 --> 00:32.658
♪

00:35.118 --> 00:39.873
♪

00:39.873 --> 00:41.667
[Wrigley chuckles]

00:44.586 --> 00:50.425
[Diana moaning]
[Wrigley breathing heavily]

01:03.397 --> 01:06.817
♪ Beck's <i>Go It Alone</i> playing ♪

01:06.817 --> 01:09.987
♪

01:09.987 --> 01:13.866
[students chattering]

01:13.866 --> 01:16.118
♪

01:16.118 --> 01:18.245
<i>♪ I'm coming over ♪</i>

01:18.245 --> 01:20.747
<i>♪ See me down at the station
by the lane ♪</i>

01:20.747 --> 01:22.749
<i>♪ With my hands in my pocket ♪</i>

01:22.749 --> 01:24.751
<i>♪ Jingling a wish coin ♪</i>

01:24.751 --> 01:27.171
<i>♪ That I stole from a fountain
that was drownin' ♪</i>

01:27.171 --> 01:28.964
<i>♪ All the cares in the world ♪</i>

01:28.964 --> 01:31.008
<i>♪ When I get older ♪</i>

01:31.008 --> 01:33.594
<i>♪ Climbing up on the back porch fence ♪</i>

01:33.594 --> 01:35.429
<i>♪ Just to see the dogs runnin' ♪</i>

01:35.429 --> 01:37.556
<i>♪ With a ring and a question ♪</i>

01:37.556 --> 01:41.185
<i>♪ And my shivering voice is singing
through a crack in the window ♪</i>

01:41.185 --> 01:42.644
<i>♪ Na na na na na na ♪</i>

01:43.854 --> 01:46.148
<i>♪ I better go it alone ♪</i>

01:46.148 --> 01:47.316
GIRL:
Hey!

01:47.316 --> 01:48.567
Are you Lucy?

01:48.567 --> 01:49.776
- Yeah.

01:49.776 --> 01:51.445
- I'm your new roommate, Charlie.

01:52.237 --> 01:55.199
They told you I was coming, right?
- Yes, I'm, I'm so sorry.

01:55.199 --> 01:56.116
Yeah, hi.

01:56.116 --> 01:57.618
- Nice to meet you.

01:57.618 --> 01:59.620
Is that my bed?

01:59.620 --> 02:00.537
- Yes.

02:00.537 --> 02:02.289
Um, I'm sorry.

02:02.289 --> 02:03.874
I'll, I'll move all of that.

02:06.376 --> 02:07.419
- I'll help you out.

02:09.046 --> 02:10.297
[phone ringing]

02:10.297 --> 02:13.217
<i>♪ Lookin' back at the sky
it's burning in the rearview mirror ♪</i>

02:13.217 --> 02:14.635
<i>♪ Na na na na na na ♪</i>

02:15.802 --> 02:16.929
[ringing continues]

02:16.929 --> 02:18.388
<i>♪ I better go it alone ♪</i>

02:19.181 --> 02:21.141
<i>♪ Na na na na na na ♪</i>

02:22.267 --> 02:25.562
<i>♪ I better go it alone ♪</i>

02:25.562 --> 02:26.480
<i>♪ Na na na na na na ♪</i>

02:26.480 --> 02:27.439
- Hey, man.

02:27.439 --> 02:29.024
- Hey.
- Happy new year.

02:29.024 --> 02:31.068
- Hey, you too, dude.
WRIGLEY: Hey!

02:31.068 --> 02:32.778
Oh my god, let me get in here.

02:33.195 --> 02:34.404
[Wrigley laughs]

02:34.988 --> 02:37.783
- Hey.
[Wrigley grunting]

02:39.368 --> 02:41.662
I'm so happy I'm getting a semi.
[chuckling]

02:44.540 --> 02:45.749
You haven't been answering my texts.

02:45.749 --> 02:48.001
- I know, I'm sorry, dude.
I've just been

02:48.544 --> 02:52.589
so in the family shit, you know.

02:52.589 --> 02:53.882
- That's alright. I forgive you.

02:53.882 --> 02:54.925
- Yeah.

02:56.134 --> 02:57.219
- So how was your Christmas?

02:57.219 --> 02:58.804
<i>♪ Na na na na na na ♪</i>

02:59.972 --> 03:03.183
<i>♪ I better go it alone ♪</i>

03:03.183 --> 03:05.602
<i>♪ Na na na na na na ♪</i>

03:06.270 --> 03:09.815
<i>♪ I better go it alone ♪</i>

03:09.815 --> 03:11.358
<i>♪ Na na na na na na ♪</i>

03:14.111 --> 03:16.488
BREE:
Maybe this. Ooh, what about this?

03:16.488 --> 03:19.241
- Okay, so did you, like, talk
to Evan on the phone?

03:19.241 --> 03:20.868
BREE:
No, no, we just texted.

03:20.868 --> 03:21.702
PIPPA:
Aw.

03:21.702 --> 03:25.330
- It's weird. Like, we talk a lot,
but he won't make any moves.

03:26.582 --> 03:27.583
What do you think?

03:29.126 --> 03:30.460
- About Evan?

03:30.460 --> 03:34.131
I think he'd be an idiot
not to fall in love with you.

03:34.131 --> 03:36.008
- Oh my god, I can make
a skirt out of this.

03:36.008 --> 03:37.092
- Did you think of a costume yet?

03:37.092 --> 03:39.511
- I'm, I'm still not really
fully understanding

03:39.511 --> 03:41.430
the concept behind this party.

03:41.430 --> 03:42.681
- It's anything but clothes.

03:42.681 --> 03:45.350
So you can make a costume out of anything

03:45.350 --> 03:47.186
except for regular clothes.

03:47.186 --> 03:48.312
- Oh.

03:48.312 --> 03:50.063
- So like any of this shit is allowed.

03:50.063 --> 03:51.273
- Mm-hmm, yeah.
LUCY: Got it.

03:52.816 --> 03:55.319
- Everybody goes, so don't be lame.

03:55.319 --> 03:57.821
- I will find something.
I have all week.

03:57.821 --> 03:58.989
- So I told Wrigley

03:58.989 --> 04:02.409
I would go to this party
off campus tonight.

04:02.409 --> 04:04.036
Do you guys wanna come?

04:04.036 --> 04:05.579
BREE:
I can't. I have class at nine a.m.

04:05.579 --> 04:08.832
- Yeah, I have my advanced fiction class
pretty early too.

04:08.832 --> 04:09.791
- Wait, you got into that?

04:09.791 --> 04:11.376
- Yeah, I didn't tell you?

04:11.376 --> 04:13.378
BREE:
No, you definitely didn't!

04:13.378 --> 04:14.338
Are you excited?

04:14.338 --> 04:15.923
- Yeah, no, I am.

04:15.923 --> 04:17.049
I'm really excited.

04:19.218 --> 04:22.137
- So did you see Stephen over break?

04:25.724 --> 04:26.558
- No.

04:28.268 --> 04:29.645
No, I did not.

04:33.857 --> 04:34.983
I think I'm, uh,

04:36.610 --> 04:39.029
done with him for now.

04:40.322 --> 04:41.323
- Seriously?

04:42.991 --> 04:44.451
- Yeah, seriously.

04:46.411 --> 04:48.622
- Fucking finally, dude!
- God!

04:48.622 --> 04:49.831
PIPPA:
I am so relieved, dude.

04:49.831 --> 04:51.416
- That's genuinely great news.

04:51.416 --> 04:53.502
- You have no idea how long
we've waited for you to do this.

04:53.502 --> 04:54.795
We talk about it all the time.

04:54.795 --> 04:57.130
- Not, like, all the time.

04:57.130 --> 04:58.715
- No, we talk about it a lot though.

04:58.715 --> 05:02.094
- Great, guys, I'm so happy to hear
how strongly you guys feel about this.

05:02.094 --> 05:03.470
- What was the final straw?

05:04.304 --> 05:06.849
- I don't know.
I-- he was just hiding a lot of stuff.

05:06.849 --> 05:09.101
I'll explain at some point.

05:09.101 --> 05:11.812
I just need to process it all first.

05:12.980 --> 05:14.273
[knocking on door]
- Hey.

05:14.273 --> 05:15.482
LUCY: Hey.
- I heard your voice in here.

05:15.482 --> 05:18.068
LUCY: Hi!
Charlie, this is Bree and Pippa.

05:18.068 --> 05:18.944
BREE AND PIPPA:
Hi.

05:18.944 --> 05:20.028
- Nice to meet you.

05:20.028 --> 05:22.030
- So, uh,
where did you transfer from?

05:22.030 --> 05:23.115
- SUNY Purchase.

05:23.115 --> 05:24.283
I was there for dance,

05:24.283 --> 05:26.618
and I fucked up my knee
for, like, the fifth time.

05:26.618 --> 05:28.954
- Oh.
- Yeah, I gotta find a new direction.

05:28.954 --> 05:31.582
- That, uh, really sucks.

05:31.582 --> 05:33.542
- But what is all of this?

05:33.542 --> 05:34.585
[Bree and Pippa chuckle]

05:34.585 --> 05:37.546
- Have you heard of
an anything but clothes party?

05:37.546 --> 05:40.090
- I have, but I thought it was like

05:40.090 --> 05:42.718
a heterosexual urban legend.

05:43.760 --> 05:47.347
- Yeah. Right, well, uh,
Theta Mu hosts one every year.

05:47.347 --> 05:48.849
You should definitely come.
BREE: Yeah.

05:48.849 --> 05:51.476
- I don't think I have anything
for a costume but, um--

05:51.476 --> 05:53.937
PIPPA: Uh, there's an amazing
dollar store in town.

05:53.937 --> 05:56.940
I need some more stuff,
so I'll go with you tomorrow if you want.

05:56.940 --> 05:59.067
- Yeah!
Yeah, that sounds great.

05:59.860 --> 06:00.861
- Okay, cool.

06:12.372 --> 06:13.665
- Oh my god, cute shorts.

06:14.708 --> 06:15.959
- What's wrong with these shorts?

06:15.959 --> 06:17.461
They are a respectable length.

06:17.878 --> 06:18.879
I asked several people.

06:18.879 --> 06:20.214
- What kind of people?

06:20.214 --> 06:21.048
[chuckles]

06:22.216 --> 06:23.509
- I'm gonna work out with Wrigley.

06:23.967 --> 06:26.428
- Huh. Why?
EVAN: Yeah, I don't know.

06:26.970 --> 06:28.472
I'm regretting it already.

06:28.472 --> 06:30.015
- He takes it too seriously.

06:30.933 --> 06:32.851
He's a quarterback at a tier two school.

06:33.393 --> 06:34.811
He's not gonna go pro.

06:40.526 --> 06:41.693
[phone buzzes]

06:46.698 --> 06:47.991
Hey.

06:47.991 --> 06:48.825
EVAN:
Yo.

06:51.870 --> 06:53.038
- I'll, uh,

06:53.997 --> 06:55.791
I'll go with you.
- Cool, yeah.

06:55.791 --> 06:57.042
We can be humiliated together.

06:57.042 --> 07:00.045
- Oh, it's not possible for me
to be humiliated by Wrigley.

07:02.005 --> 07:04.508
- Hopefully, you all got
your rest in over the break

07:04.508 --> 07:07.427
because there's gonna be
a lot of work this semester.

07:08.387 --> 07:10.514
If you'll take out your copies
of <i>On Writing,</i>

07:10.514 --> 07:13.183
I'm excited to hear
what everyone thought of it so far.

07:15.602 --> 07:16.436
Lucy.

07:17.813 --> 07:19.147
You do not have a copy?

07:19.147 --> 07:21.108
- We were supposed to have that
for the first class?

07:21.108 --> 07:22.067
- Yes.

07:23.026 --> 07:23.944
- I'm sorry.

07:23.944 --> 07:25.779
I, um, I'll catch up today.

07:28.574 --> 07:29.950
- Woo!

07:29.950 --> 07:31.076
Fighting Owls!

07:31.660 --> 07:32.578
Hoot-hoot!

07:33.328 --> 07:34.955
Come on, bitch boys, keep it going!

07:34.955 --> 07:37.833
Are you hurting? [laughing]

07:39.042 --> 07:39.960
Alright.

07:42.379 --> 07:44.923
[Evan coughing]

07:51.138 --> 07:54.141
[Evan grunting]

07:54.141 --> 07:55.434
[Wrigley laughs]
EVAN: Fuck!

07:55.434 --> 07:56.560
Fuck you, Wrigley.

07:59.938 --> 08:01.356
[grunting] Fuck!

08:01.356 --> 08:02.357
I'm done, I'm out.

08:04.651 --> 08:05.611
- You look so pretty.

08:05.611 --> 08:07.529
If we ever go to prison,
I promise to protect you.

08:08.155 --> 08:08.989
[Wrigley chuckles]

08:08.989 --> 08:12.743
[panting]

08:21.126 --> 08:22.002
- What are you--
what are you doing?

08:22.002 --> 08:23.086
- I got it, Wrigley.

08:23.086 --> 08:25.047
- No, no, no. Come on, seriously,
that's too heavy for you.

08:25.047 --> 08:26.006
Cut it out.

08:26.006 --> 08:27.508
- Can you back up?
Can you let me try?

08:29.676 --> 08:30.677
- At least let me spot you.

08:31.428 --> 08:33.472
I'll spot you.
Okay, I'll spot you.

08:35.516 --> 08:36.517
[grunts]

08:37.017 --> 08:38.310
Whoa, okay, yeah.

08:38.310 --> 08:40.103
- I got it, I got it, I got, I got it.
- Alright, alright?

08:40.103 --> 08:41.313
- Yeah, I got it.

08:43.106 --> 08:45.275
[exhales forcefully]

08:45.275 --> 08:46.193
[grunting]

08:46.193 --> 08:47.361
- You're done, you're done!

08:47.361 --> 08:48.237
Jesus!

08:49.112 --> 08:50.739
[panting]

08:50.739 --> 08:52.324
- Jesus Christ, dude,
you could have smashed your ribs.

08:52.324 --> 08:53.992
That's not smart. That's not good.
- Ah, fuck.

08:59.623 --> 09:01.458
PROFESSOR: Your short story
can be about anything,

09:01.458 --> 09:04.294
but it must take place
in a time of crisis.

09:04.294 --> 09:05.462
It can be any time of crisis.

09:05.462 --> 09:08.215
It can be mental, physical,
whatever that means to you.

09:08.674 --> 09:09.967
Due Thursday.

09:13.554 --> 09:15.764
- Hi. Do you have <i>On Writing?</i>

09:18.058 --> 09:19.351
It's by Stephen King.

09:20.602 --> 09:21.436
- I know.

09:24.857 --> 09:27.442
The earliest we can get it here is Monday.

09:27.442 --> 09:28.443
- Do you wanna order it?

09:28.443 --> 09:29.653
- Monday? Shit.

09:29.653 --> 09:32.281
Uh, yeah, yeah,
I'll, I'll just order it now.

09:32.281 --> 09:33.490
Thanks.

09:33.490 --> 09:37.160
♪

09:37.160 --> 09:38.579
[clattering]

09:38.579 --> 09:39.496
[sighs]

09:40.080 --> 09:44.126
♪

09:44.126 --> 09:47.671
♪

09:52.426 --> 09:53.302
- Hey.

09:54.803 --> 09:56.388
- Hey.
EVAN: How's it going?

09:56.388 --> 09:57.389
- Good, how, how are you?

09:57.389 --> 09:58.557
EVAN:
Yeah, good.

09:58.557 --> 09:59.600
- Good.

09:59.600 --> 10:00.893
- How was Christmas?

10:00.893 --> 10:02.519
- Uh, it was fine.

10:02.519 --> 10:04.188
It was weird.

10:04.188 --> 10:05.439
- What books are you getting?

10:05.439 --> 10:07.482
- Um, I, I needed <i>On Writing,</i>

10:07.482 --> 10:08.901
but they're out of stock, which is great

10:08.901 --> 10:12.529
because I looked like
a complete idiot in class today,

10:12.529 --> 10:13.864
which felt awesome.

10:13.864 --> 10:16.408
- [laughing] I'm sure you were fine.

10:16.408 --> 10:18.202
LUCY: Eh--
- But I have a copy if you want.

10:18.202 --> 10:19.369
- You do? Seriously?

10:19.369 --> 10:21.455
Oh my god.
- Yeah, yeah. I needed it last semester.

10:21.455 --> 10:22.915
- Yes.
- Yeah, it's in my dorm room.

10:22.915 --> 10:25.000
So whenever you wanna
come back and see Stephen,

10:25.834 --> 10:26.793
you'll have a book.

10:29.796 --> 10:30.631
- Yeah.

10:31.757 --> 10:35.052
Yeah, I'm not, not really dying
to see him

10:35.469 --> 10:36.428
at the moment.

10:38.847 --> 10:40.182
- Oh, okay.

10:40.182 --> 10:41.475
Yeah, yeah, sure, I get it.

10:42.559 --> 10:43.810
I mean,
[chuckles]

10:44.520 --> 10:47.731
I love the guy, but you deserve a medal
for putting up with him if I'm honest.

10:48.232 --> 10:50.776
- Yeah, maybe,
maybe we both do.

10:52.027 --> 10:53.487
- [laughing] Yeah, maybe.

10:53.946 --> 10:56.240
You know, in hindsight,
it's probably not a good idea

10:56.240 --> 10:57.616
to room with your friend.

10:57.616 --> 10:58.825
You see a lot of shit.

10:59.785 --> 11:00.619
- Yeah.

11:05.290 --> 11:09.378
Honestly, I... I think
it's over between us.

11:11.713 --> 11:12.548
- Yeah, sure.

11:13.048 --> 11:15.300
I mean, I,
I won't, I won't say anything.

11:16.134 --> 11:17.302
- Thanks.

11:17.302 --> 11:18.929
- But yeah, I can, uh,

11:18.929 --> 11:21.056
I can grab the book for you
and bring it to you.

11:22.933 --> 11:26.770
- Yeah, I have class all day,
but maybe we can grab some coffee later.

11:26.770 --> 11:27.980
- Yeah. Yeah, sure.

11:27.980 --> 11:30.440
- Okay, cool.
Thank you so much, seriously.

11:36.822 --> 11:37.656
DIANA:
Hey.

11:39.658 --> 11:41.702
I haven't seen you since we got back.

11:41.702 --> 11:43.161
- It's only been 24 hours.

11:45.664 --> 11:46.498
- I know.

11:49.418 --> 11:50.669
I missed you though.

11:52.629 --> 11:55.757
Kind of missing you right now, actually.

11:59.636 --> 12:00.512
- Oh yeah?

12:00.929 --> 12:01.805
- Mm-hmm.

12:02.848 --> 12:05.767
I have an hour till my next class.

12:08.228 --> 12:09.146
- Yeah, I don't have time.

12:09.146 --> 12:11.815
I only have half an hour
till my next class, so--

12:12.941 --> 12:14.151
- Are you sure?
- Yeah.

12:15.736 --> 12:16.778
- That isn't like you.

12:19.031 --> 12:20.199
It's been too long.

12:30.501 --> 12:31.710
- We could go in there.

12:32.211 --> 12:35.631
- Getting caught in the library
isn't really a kink of mine.

12:37.090 --> 12:39.218
- Okay, well, then I guess
it's gonna have to wait then.

12:44.848 --> 12:45.724
- Does it lock?

12:45.724 --> 12:48.519
[Stephen grunting]

12:48.519 --> 12:49.520
- Look at me.

12:54.691 --> 12:56.485
[Stephen grunting]

12:57.653 --> 13:00.113
- [grunting] Fuck!

13:09.915 --> 13:14.628
♪

13:18.632 --> 13:19.466
[door opens]

13:23.720 --> 13:27.099
♪

13:27.099 --> 13:28.225
[indiscernible chatter]

13:28.225 --> 13:33.522
♪

13:36.859 --> 13:40.028
- [laughing] But yeah,
I can officially say

13:40.028 --> 13:42.906
that I have punched somebody
in the face.

13:42.906 --> 13:43.991
- Wow.

13:43.991 --> 13:46.910
- And I gotta say, I feel,
I feel different, you know?

13:47.327 --> 13:50.330
- Oh, I don't.
I have never punched someone before.

13:50.330 --> 13:52.833
- Well, you should try it.
It's very freeing.

13:54.751 --> 13:56.003
- I don't think you
and me punching someone

13:56.003 --> 13:57.379
are the same thing.

13:59.006 --> 14:00.382
- That's fair.

14:00.382 --> 14:01.967
[Evan chuckles]

14:03.385 --> 14:05.596
- So how, how is Stephen doing?

14:05.596 --> 14:08.265
- [chuckles] I was waiting on that.

14:08.765 --> 14:11.310
- I just mean... like--

14:11.310 --> 14:13.145
- Lucy, come on.

14:15.189 --> 14:17.149
We've never gone for coffee before.

14:19.151 --> 14:20.068
It's all good.

14:22.029 --> 14:24.198
- Yeah, I just don't,
I just don't really have anyone

14:24.198 --> 14:26.658
to talk, talk about him with,
you know.

14:28.118 --> 14:28.994
So--

14:31.038 --> 14:32.581
- [sighs] So what's up?

14:33.415 --> 14:34.416
Are you avoiding him?

14:35.959 --> 14:39.379
- I just feel like there's so much stuff
I don't know about him,

14:39.379 --> 14:43.800
and I'm, I'm trying
to make peace with that.

14:43.800 --> 14:47.054
And I, I just, I know you can't
tell me everything but--

14:47.054 --> 14:48.597
- Yeah, he's one of my best friends.

14:49.139 --> 14:50.557
- I know. I know.

14:57.481 --> 15:01.485
But there's a lot of...
shit he's not telling me,

15:02.653 --> 15:03.612
isn't there?

15:12.955 --> 15:14.414
Please, just

15:17.125 --> 15:18.710
give me anything.

15:20.212 --> 15:22.381
Like, he lies to me a lot.

15:23.757 --> 15:24.675
[sighs]

15:29.179 --> 15:30.889
- But that's not surprising to you.

15:32.266 --> 15:33.851
You're not an oblivious person.

15:36.270 --> 15:37.980
